class TextEditor {
    private StringBuilder sb;
    private int pos;

    public TextEditor() {
        sb = new StringBuilder();
        pos = 0;
    }

    public void addText(String text) {
        sb.insert(pos, text);
        pos += text.length();
    }

    public int deleteText(int k) {
        int del = Math.min(k, pos);
        sb.delete(pos - del, pos);
        pos -= del;
        return del;
    }

    public String cursorLeft(int k) {
        pos = Math.max(0, pos - k);
        int start = Math.max(0, pos - 10);
        return sb.substring(start, pos);
    }

    public String cursorRight(int k) {
        pos = Math.min(sb.length(), pos + k);
        int start = Math.max(0, pos - 10);
        return sb.substring(start, pos);
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(k) per operation (k is the length of text or the integer argument)
space complexity: O(n) where n is the total characters stored
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a single StringBuilder to represent the text and an int for cursor position. All operations are direct insert/delete/move with substring for the last 10 characters, achieving O(k) per call as required by the follow-up.

